    </draw:frame>Vediamo quali sono i risultati al variare dello sfasamento <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> tra i due cammini.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="7" draw:name="Text Box 42" draw:style-name="gr2" draw:text-style-name="P4" svg:width="0.8004in" svg:height="0.4004in" svg:x="5.6189in" svg:y="0.3071in">
     <text:p text:style-name="Frame_20_contents">Fig.11</text:p>
     <draw:enhanced-geometry draw:mirror-horizontal="false" draw:mirror-vertical="false" draw:glue-points="?f0 0 0 ?f1 ?f0 ?f2 ?f3 ?f1" draw:text-areas="0 0 ?f3 ?f2" svg:viewBox="0 0 0 0" draw:type="ooxml-rect" draw:enhanced-path="M 0 0 L ?f3 0 ?f3 ?f2 0 ?f2 Z N">
      <draw:equation draw:name="f0" draw:formula="logwidth/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f1" draw:formula="logheight/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f2" draw:formula="logheight"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f3" draw:formula="logwidth"/>
     </draw:enhanced-geometry>
    </draw:custom-shape>Se lo sfasamento è nullo in uscita abbiamo lo stato <text:span text:style-name="T2">m</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">0</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">=+k </text:span>esattamente come nell’esperimento precedente, ma se lo sfasamento è diverso da zero abbiamo uno stato diverso. Se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> diviene pari ad una certa lunghezza caratteristica <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>, in uscita abbiamo di nuovo <text:span text:style-name="T2">m</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">0</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">=+k</text:span>, anche se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> è multiplo di <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>=2<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>,3<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>, ecc. abbiamo ancora lo stato <text:span text:style-name="T2">m</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">0</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">=+k. </text:span>Se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> è pari a <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>/2 in uscita abbiamo lo stato <text:span text:style-name="T2">m</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">0</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">=-k</text:span>!</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">In generale per le probabilità abbiamo le seguenti formule:</text:p>
