   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per concludere rivediamo i principi fondamentali che abbiamo individuato.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">Principi della Meccanica Quantistica (versione semplificata).</text:h>
   <text:list text:style-name="WWNum1">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P9">Un sistema fisico è caratterizzato dalle sue grandezze fisiche che possono essere misurate.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P9">Quando si misura una grandezza <text:span text:style-name="T2">g</text:span> sono possibili diversi risultati, ed ogni risultato ha una certa probabilità di uscire. Se dalla misura si ottiene un particolare risultato <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object154" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4835in" svg:height="0.2335in"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAkAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAfgBAAAL
         AQAAJAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAP//gQABABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPcBAAAKAQAAiwAB
         AAIAAAAAGJUAAQAEAAAAAAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
         AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
         AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
         DAAAANcAAAABAGd4AAAAAAABAAEAZwCMAAEAAAAAAIsAAQACAAAAHwCKAAEAQgAAAAUAPAAA
         AAoAT3BlblN5bWJvbAAAAAAAAPAAAAD//wAAAAAFAAAAAAAAAP8DAAAAAAAAAAEA/wMAAAAA
         AAAAAAAAAIgAAQACAAAAAQCHAAEABQAAAP////8AhgABAAQAAAAAAAAAcgACABoAAACQAAAA
         1wAAAAEAAAA9AL8AAAAAAAEAAQA9AIwAAQAAAAAAiwABAAIAAAAfAIoAAQBCAAAABQA8AAAA
         CgBPcGVuU3ltYm9sAAAAAAAA8AAAAP//AAAAAAUAAAAAAAAA/wMAAAAAAAAAAQD/AwAAAAAA
         AAAAAAAAiAABAAIAAAABAIcAAQAFAAAA/////wCGAAEABAAAAAAAAAByAAIAGgAAAFwBAADn
         AAAAAQAAAK8AeAAAAAAAAQABAK8AjAABAAAAAACLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
         AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
         AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
         YQEAANcAAAABAGd4AAAAAAABAAEAZwCMAAEAAAAAAIwAAQAAAAAAjAABAAAAAAA=
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>, il sistema si porta in uno stato tale che, se si ripete la misura di <text:span text:style-name="T2">g</text:span> si ottiene con certezza il valore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object155" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4835in" svg:height="0.2335in"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAkAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAfgBAAAL
         AQAAJAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAP//gQABABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAPcBAAAKAQAAiwAB
         AAIAAAAAGJUAAQAEAAAAAAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
         AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
         AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
         DAAAANcAAAABAGd4AAAAAAABAAEAZwCMAAEAAAAAAIsAAQACAAAAHwCKAAEAQgAAAAUAPAAA
         AAoAT3BlblN5bWJvbAAAAAAAAPAAAAD//wAAAAAFAAAAAAAAAP8DAAAAAAAAAAEA/wMAAAAA
         AAAAAAAAAIgAAQACAAAAAQCHAAEABQAAAP////8AhgABAAQAAAAAAAAAcgACABoAAACQAAAA
         1wAAAAEAAAA9AL8AAAAAAAEAAQA9AIwAAQAAAAAAiwABAAIAAAAfAIoAAQBCAAAABQA8AAAA
         CgBPcGVuU3ltYm9sAAAAAAAA8AAAAP//AAAAAAUAAAAAAAAA/wMAAAAAAAAAAQD/AwAAAAAA
         AAAAAAAAiAABAAIAAAABAIcAAQAFAAAA/////wCGAAEABAAAAAAAAAByAAIAGgAAAFwBAADn
         AAAAAQAAAK8AeAAAAAAAAQABAK8AjAABAAAAAACLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
         AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
         AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
         YQEAANcAAAABAGd4AAAAAAABAAEAZwCMAAEAAAAAAIwAAQAAAAAAjAABAAAAAAA=
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>. Un tale stato viene detto autostato di <text:span text:style-name="T2">g</text:span> con autovalore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object156" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1835in" svg:height="0.2335in"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mover accent="true">
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
            </mover>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAkAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAaMAAAAL
         AQAAFgAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAP//gQABABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKIAAAAKAQAAiwAB
         AAIAAAAAGJUAAQAEAAAAAAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEIAAAAFADwAAAAK
         AE9wZW5TeW1ib2wAAAAAAADwAAAA//8AAAAABQAAAAAAAAD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8DAAAAAAAA
         AAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAaAAAABwAAAOcA
